turer  wikipedia herman miller manufacturer from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search herman miller inc type public traded as nasdaq mlhr sp  component industry furniture manufacturing office and home furnishings retailer predecessor star furniture co michigan star furniture co herman miller furniture company founded zeeland michigan united states   founder d j depree headquarters zeeland michigan united states area served worldwide revenue  billion  operating income  million  net income  million  subsidiaries design within reach geiger maharam website hermanmillercom herman miller inc based in zeeland michigan is a major american manufacturer of office furniture equipment and home furnishings it is notable as one of the first companies to produce modern furniture and under the guidance of design director george nelson is likely the most prolific and influential producer of furniture of the modernist style among classic herman miller products are the equa chair aeron chair noguchi table marshmallow sofa and the eames lounge chair herman miller is credited with the invention of the office cubicle originally known as the action office ii in  under thendirector of research robert propst herman miller holds a unique position among furniture manufacturers for having cultivated the talents of a large number of modernist designers producing a significant number of pieces that are now considered icons of industrial design contents  history  workplace  sustainability  notable products  seating  tablesdesks  references  external links historyedit a typical distribution depot in chippenham wiltshire herman miller was founded in  as the star furniture co in zeeland michigan initially the company produced high quality furniture especially bedroom suites in historic revival styles in  dirk jan de pree began working for the company as a clerk and became its president by  when it was renamed the michigan star furniture co de pree and his fatherinlaw herman miller purchased  of the company stock in  and renamed it the herman miller furniture company it became herman miller inc in  until  the company produced only traditional wood furniture with the coming of the great depression the company was forced to explore new products to survive in a shrinking market and reluctantly hired gilbert rohde a designer who specialized in modernist designs rohde turned the company in a totally new direction and in  herman miller debuted a line of modern furniture at the century of progress exposition in chicago illinois in  the company opened a showroom in the merchandise mart in chicago and another in new york city under rohdes supervision herman miller entered the contract office furniture market in  with the introduction of the modular executive office group eog the first in a long line of office furnishings to be produced by the company rohde died in  and was replaced by architect george nelson who joined the firm as director of design in  over the next four decades nelson was to have an enormous influence upon herman miller not only for his personal design contributions but also for the talented designers he recruited to its ranks including isamu noguchi charles and ray eames robert propst and textile designer alexander girard beginning in the late s the period under nelsons guidance saw herman miller produce some of the worlds most iconic pieces of modern furniture including the noguchi table eames lounge chair marshmallow sofa ball clock actually produced by howard miller clock company and the sling sofa dirk jan de pree continued to serve as herman miller ceo until  when he was forced by illness to step down he was succeeded by his son hugh de pree hugh served as company ceo until the mids when he was succeeded by his brother max de pree who held the position until  in  herman miller set up the herman miller research division based in ann arbor michigan this division developed the action office line in  under the supervision of robert propst and with the design assistance of george nelsons new york design studio though the initial line known as action office i was not a success it led propst to develop the action office ii line which introduced the office cubicle the impact of action office ii on the workplace revolutionized the office environment in  action office ii was renamed simply action office herman millers line of action office products generated sales of over  billion as of update george nelsons influence at herman miller gradually declined during the s as new designers joined the company including don chadwick and bill stumpf who codesigned the equa chair still widely marketed and in the s developed the highlysuccessful aeron chair in  herman miller started to work with the italian designer clino t castelli on the process of designing physical environments a socalled design primario including cmf design and ethospace design concept designer tom newhouse introduced the newhouse group of freestanding furniture in  and assisted with the ethospace wall panel system for the action office line ray wilkes designed the modular seating group popularly known as the chicklet chairs artist stephen frykholm is also noted for his contributions to herman miller from  to  frykholm produced a series of promotional posters for herman millers annual summer picnics some of which are in the permanent collections of the museum of modern art and remain highly soughtafter art prints in july  herman miller announced it had reached an agreement to purchase the contemporary retailer design within reach dwr for  million in a bid to establish itself as a “premier lifestyle brand” workplaceedit herman miller is consistently recognized as one of fortune magazines most admired companies having placed at the top of the list for furniture companies for the past  consecutive yearswhen according to cnn money as of march update herman miller was ranked as the second most admired company in the home equipment furnishing division they also scored first in innovation people management use of corporate assets social responsibility and quality of productsservices in quality of management they scored second place third in long term investments fourth in financial soundness and ninth in global competitiveness in march  they settled an antitrust lawsuit with the states of new york michigan and illinois for  the lawsuit focused on herman millers use of a suggested retail pricing policy which was found to be within the bounds of the law today many companies employ such policies to avoid price erosion in the internet channel sustainabilityedit herman miller has engaged in a number of initiatives to promote sustainability and many of them have had costsaving implications for the company the company has developed a technique of mixing sawdust with chicken manure to produce topsoil the company also uses a database to track every chemical in each product used by the company in order to eliminate harmful chemicals from their products management of the company has expressed concerns about global warming and the company was using  renewable energy as of update the company also issues a sustainability report herman millers driving sustainability initiatives is its perfect vision goal this is a broad initiative that sets significant targets for the year  these targets include zero landfill disposal zero hazardous waste generation zero air emissions vocs zero process water discharge  green electrical energy use company buildings constructed to a minimum leed silver certification and  of sales from dfeapprovedclarification needed products many of herman millers products are designed to be ecologically sound and many are good examples of ecodesign techniques for achieving sustainability include saving materials energy efficient manufacturing recycled content and recyclable content including design for disassembly the design process also utilizes life cycle assessmentcitation needed herman miller helped fund the start of the united states green building council and hired architect william mcdonough  partners to design a factory incorporating green design principles the building is known as the greenhouse and is an example of green building the building won the following awards aia committee on the environment top ten environmental buildings  business weekarchitectural record good design is good business award  aia central virginia honor award  international development research council award for distinguished service in environmental planning  notable productsedit the aeron chair seatingedit ergon    designed by bill stumpf equa    designed by bill stumpf and don chadwick aeron chair  – designed by bill stumpf and don chadwick eames aluminum group chairs  – designed by charles and ray eames eames lounge chair and ottoman  – designed by charles and ray eames eames lounge chair wood  – designed by charles and ray eames marshmallow sofa  – designed by irving harper celle  – designed by jerome caruso embody  – designed by bill stumpf and jeff weber setu  – designed by studio  sayl  – designed by yves behar mirra   – designed by studio  remastered aeron  tablesdesksedit noguchi table  – designed by isamu noguchi referencesedit  schlosser julie march   cubicles the great mistake fortune magazine   a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u pina leslie  classic herman miller atglen pennsylvania schiffer publishing isbn    victor margolin design discourse history theory criticism chicago illinois university of chicago press   sam hall kaplan west week spotlights furniture april   los angeles times  herman miller announces agreement to acquire design within reach  worlds most admired companies  herman miller snapshot cnn   herman miller states settle suit on aeron chair price muskegon chronicle   tim zaun herman miller the bhag and internalizing sustainability greenerdesign greenbizcom jun    our vision  herman miller  herman miller embraces nature and engages our youth huffington post july     “greenhouse” factory  offices  william mcdonough  partners external linksedit official herman miller company website cnncom cubicles the great mistake youtubecom comments on herman miller — by designer yves béhar v t e herman miller people don chadwick charles and ray eames alexander girard george nelson isamu noguchi robert propst gilbert rohde bill stumpf products action office aeron chair eames lounge chair marshmallow sofa mirra chair noguchi table v t e charles and ray eames architecture eames house exhibitions mathematica a world of numbers and beyond films toccata for toy trains  powers of ten   furniture eames lounge chair wood eames lounge chair eames fiberglass armchair eames aluminum group other eames the architect and the painter good design awards the india report herman miller retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlehermanmillermanufactureroldid categories furniture companies of the united statesfurniture manufacturersdesign companies of the united statesindustrial design firmsmanufacturing companies based in michiganottawa county michiganzeeland michigandesign companies established in manufacturing companies established in  establishments in michigancompanies listed on nasdaqmodernist architecture in michiganhidden categories articles containing potentially dated statements from all articles containing potentially dated statementsall articles with vague or ambiguous timevague or ambiguous time from december articles containing potentially dated statements from march articles containing potentially dated statements from wikipedia articles needing clarification from may all articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from february  navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interact